foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: APHIS - Five cases were inadvertently closed out of the database system in FY09 while they were actually still pending at the end of FY09, therefore making 462 the actual starting number of pending requests at the beginning of FY10.

FSA - The number of request pending at the end of fiscal year 2009 was incorrect. It should have been reported as 141. This is because 29 Privacy Act requests were incorrectly entered into the system in fiscal year 2009, as FOIA requests. They were deleted prior to the start of fiscal year 2010. (This also reduces the number of FOIA requests received in fiscal year 2009 to 6416).

ASCR - Two cases were inadvertently closed out of the database system in FY09 while they were actually still pending at the end of FY09, therefore making 2 the actual starting number of pending requests at the beginning of FY10.

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: FNCS - Number of appeals pending as of start of FY10 is different from the FY09 annual report due to an appeal being found that was never answered.
APHIS - Two appelas which were actually closed in FY09 were not updated in the database system until FY10, making the number of pending appeals at the end of FY09 '70' not '72'.
FSA - The number of appeals reported pending in FY09 was reported as 6. The correct number should have been 7.

FS - Some reporting inconsistencies may be attributable to the three different migrations of data actions from a proprietary tracking system to the newly procured FOIAXpress system. The national backlog increase may have been caused by either the data migration or the more accurate system capturing "open" cases as backlog.
